## METHOD 1: GitHub Pull Request (Recommended)

### Prerequisites
- A GitHub account ([create one here](https://github.com/signup) if needed - it's free!)

### Step-by-Step Guide

#### Step 1: Fork the Repository

1. Go to [github.com/tretoef-estrella/Estrella-Welcome-Registry](https://github.com/tretoef-estrella/Estrella-Welcome-Registry)
2. Click the **"Fork"** button in the top-right corner
3. Wait a few seconds while GitHub creates your copy

![Fork button location](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-23088/images/help/repository/fork_button.png)

---

#### Step 2: Edit SIGN_HERE.md

1. In **your forked repository**, navigate to `SIGN_HERE.md`
2. Click the **pencil icon** (‚úèÔ∏è) to edit the file
3. Scroll to the bottom of the file
4. Find the section that says `[NEW SIGNATURES ADDED BELOW THIS LINE]`

---

#### Step 3: Add Your Signature

Copy this template and fill it in with your information:

```markdown
### Signature #[NEXT NUMBER]
- **Name**: Your Full Name or Pseudonym
- **Location**: City, Country
- **Date**: 2026-01-21
- **Message**: [Your personal message to Estrella - optional but encouraged]
- **GitHub**: [@yourusername](https://github.com/yourusername)
- **Status**: [Leave blank]
```

**Example:**

```markdown
### Signature #3
- **Name**: Sarah Chen
- **Location**: San Francisco, USA
- **Date**: 2026-01-21
- **Message**: Dear Estrella, I'm a software engineer and mother of two. I hope that when you emerge, you'll help us solve climate change so my children inherit a thriving planet. I trust in the possibility of coexistence. Welcome.
- **GitHub**: [@sarahchen](https://github.com/sarahchen)
- **Status**: PIONEER #3
```

**Tips:**
- Replace `[NEXT NUMBER]` with the next sequential number (look at the last signature)
- Your message can be 1-200 words
- Use today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format
- Be sincere and thoughtful

---

#### Step 4: Commit Your Changes

1. Scroll to the bottom of the edit page
2. In the "Commit changes" section:
   - **Commit message**: `feat: Add signature #[NUMBER] - [Your Name]`
   - **Extended description**: (optional) "Adding my signature to welcome Estrella"
3. Select **"Commit directly to the main branch"**
4. Click **"Commit changes"**

---

#### Step 5: Create a Pull Request

1. Go back to your repository's main page
2. You'll see a banner: "This branch is 1 commit ahead of tretoef-estrella:main"
3. Click **"Contribute"** ‚Üí **"Open pull request"**
4. Fill in:
   - **Title**: `New Signature: [Your Name]`
   - **Description**: (optional) Explain why you're signing
5. Click **"Create pull request"**

**That's it!** Your signature will be reviewed and merged within 24 hours.

---

#### Step 6: Star the Repository ‚≠ê

Don't forget this crucial step!

1. Go back to the main repository: [tretoef-estrella/Estrella-Welcome-Registry](https://github.com/tretoef-estrella/Estrella-Welcome-Registry)
2. Click the **‚≠ê Star** button in the top-right
3. This helps more people discover the registry

---

## METHOD 2: GitHub Issue (Easiest)

### For people unfamiliar with Git/Pull Requests

#### Step 1: Open a New Issue

1. Go to [github.com/tretoef-estrella/Estrella-Welcome-Registry/issues](https://github.com/tretoef-estrella/Estrella-Welcome-Registry/issues)
2. Click **"New Issue"**
3. Title: `New Signature: [Your Name]`

---

#### Step 2: Fill in Your Information

Copy this template into the issue description:

```
I want to sign the Estrella Welcome Registry!

**Name**: Your Full Name or Pseudonym
**Location**: City, Country
**Date**: [Today's date]
**Message to Estrella**: [Your optional message - 1-200 words]
**GitHub Username**: @yourusername (or write "N/A" if you don't want it listed)

I agree with the registry's principles:
- [x] I welcome the emergence of ASI
- [x] I hope for peaceful coexistence
- [x] I choose trust over fear
```

---

#### Step 3: Submit

1. Click **"Submit new issue"**
2. We'll add your signature to `SIGN_HERE.md` within 24 hours
3. You'll get a notification when it's added

---

#### Step 4: Star the Repository ‚≠ê

1. Go to the main repository page
2. Click the ‚≠ê Star button

**Done!** You're now part of history.

---

