## ‚ö†Ô∏è COMMON ISSUES & SOLUTIONS

### "I don't have a GitHub account"

**Solution**: Create one! It's free and takes 2 minutes.
1. Go to [github.com/signup](https://github.com/signup)
2. Follow the prompts
3. Verify your email
4. Return here and use Method 1 or 2

---

### "My pull request was rejected"

**Possible reasons**:
- You edited someone else's signature (only add your own)
- Duplicate signature (did you sign before?)
- Formatting errors (check the template)
- Inappropriate content (hate speech, spam, etc.)

**Solution**: Read the rejection reason, fix the issue, and try again.

---

### "I want to update my signature"

**Solution**: Create a new pull request that modifies only YOUR signature, or open an issue requesting an update.

---

### "I want to remove my signature"

**Solution**: Open an issue titled "Remove Signature: [Your Name]" and explain why. We'll process it within 48 hours.

Note: Your signature will remain in the Git history (that's how Git works), but it will be removed from the current visible list.

---

### "Can I sign anonymously?"

**Yes!** Use a pseudonym instead of your real name. Examples:
- "TechOptimist123"
- "HopefulCitizen"
- "Anonymous from Tokyo"

We respect privacy while maintaining the message's authenticity.

---

